{"title_page": "Vaibhav Mangle", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name             = Vaibhav Mangle\n| native_name      = \u0935\u0948\u092d\u0935 \u092e\u093e\u0902\u0917\u0932\u0947\n| native_name_lang = Marathi\n| birth_place      = [[Devrukh]], [[Ratnagiri]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]].      \n| birth_date       = 7 June 1975 (age 44)\n| nationality      = [[India]]n\n| occupation       = [[Actor]]\n| known_for        = \n| style            = Comedy\n}}\n\n'''Vaibhav Mangle''' ({{lang-mr|\u0935\u0948\u092d\u0935 \u092e\u093e\u0902\u0917\u0932\u0947}}) is a Marathi actor and Hindi film, television and stage actor, noted for his comic roles in Marathi theatre and Marathi films and television from India. Anand Ingle and Vaibhav Mangle are seen playing BL Pathak in Zee Marathi's TV series Shejari Shejari Pakke Shejari<ref>[http://www.sakaaltimes.com/NewsDetails.aspx?NewsId=5670859304939646445&SectionId=4924098573178130559&SectionName=Latest%20News&NewsDate=20130219&NewsTitle=Will%20the%20real%20BL%20Pathak%20stand%20up?]</ref>\n\n==Television==\nHe is well known for his skits in Fu Bai Fu, a Marathi standup comedy TV show on [[Zee Marathi]]. He also plays the main role, along with Anand Ingle, in the comedy show Shejaari Shejaari Pakke Shejaari<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://marathistars.com/tv-serial/shejari-shejari-pakke-shejari-zee-marathi-serial-cast-story-photos/|title=Shejari Shejari Pakke Shejari Zee marathi Serial Cast,Crew,Actor,Actress|first=Editorial|last=Staff|date=23 February 2013|accessdate=2 March 2019}}</ref> also aired on [[Zee Marathi]]. In this serial, he plays the character of Brijlal Pathak, also known as Birju.\n\nAlso working in Shirdi Ke Saibaba, on Sony .\n\n==Filmography==\nHis movies include ''[[Harishchandrachi Factory]]'', ''[[Kaksparsh]]'', ''[[Shikshanachya Aaicha Gho]]'',''[[Navra Maza Navsacha]]'', [[Shahanpan Dega Deva]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt2625014/fullcredits|title=Shahanpan Dega Deva (2011) - IMDb|accessdate=2 March 2019|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref> [[Fakta Ladh Mhana]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt2130033/fullcredits|title=Fakta Ladh Mhana (2011) - IMDb|accessdate=2 March 2019|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref> [[Shala]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1830802/fullcredits|title=Shala (2011) - IMDb|accessdate=2 March 2019|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref> [[Touring Talkies]], [[Timepass (film)|Timepass]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://marathistars.com/movies/touring-talkies-upcoming-marathi-movie/|title=Touring Talkies Marathi Movie,Cast,Story,photos,Promo,Trailer,official Video|first=Editorial|last=Staff|date=29 March 2013|accessdate=2 March 2019}}</ref> are some of the successful movies in which he played an important role.\n\nFollowing table shows list of films\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year !! Title !! Language !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n\n|2019|| ''[[Triple Seat]]'' ||[[Marathi language|Marathi]]||  ||\n|-\n|2015|| ''[[Timepass 2]]'' ||Marathi|| Prajakta's father Madhavrao Lele ||\n|-\n|2014|| ''[[Sanngto Aika]]'' ||Marathi || Palav||\n|-\n|2014|| ''Postcard'' ||Marathi|| ||\n|-\n|2014|| ''[[Timepass (film)|Timepass]]'' ||Marathi|| Prajakta's father (Shakal)||\n|-\n|2013|| ''[[Chaandi]]'' ||Marathi|| ||\n|-\n|2013|| ''[[Touring Talkies (film)|Touring Talkies]]'' ||[[Marathi language|Marathi]]||Shubhnya||\n|-\n|2013|| ''Kokanastha-Taath Kana Haach Baana'' ||[[Marathi language|Marathi]]||||\n|-\n|2012|| ''Pipani'' ||[[Marathi language|Marathi]]|| ||\n|-\n|2012|| ''[[Kaksparsh]]'' ||[[Marathi language|Marathi]]|| Upadhyay||\n|-\n|2012|| ''[[Shala (film)|Shala]]'' ||[[Marathi language|Marathi]]|| Ponkshe Kaka||\n|-\n|2012|| ''Kutumb'' ||[[Marathi language|Marathi]]||Sawkar ||\n|-\n|2011|| ''[[Fakta Ladh Mhana]]'' ||[[Marathi language|Marathi]]|| Sawkar Kulkarni ||\n|-\n|2011|| ''[[Shahanpan Dega Deva]]'' ||[[Marathi language|Marathi]]|| ||\n|-\n|2010|| ''[[City of Gold (2010 film)|City of Gold]]'' ||[[Marathi language|Marathi]]||DoctorSaheb ||\n|-\n|2010|| ''[[Harishchandrachi Factory]]'' ||[[Marathi language|Marathi]]||Gajabhau ||\n|-\n|2010|| ''[[Shikshanacha Aaicha Gho]]'' ||[[Marathi language|Marathi]]|| ||\n|-\n|2004|| ''[[Navra Maza Navsacha]]'' ||[[Marathi language|Marathi]]|| ||\n|-\n|}\n\n==Drama==\nHe played the main role in the Marathi play [[Ek Daav Bhatacha]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.webmallindia.com/buy-dvd-online-movie-ek-daav-bhatacha-p-1639.html|title=EK DAAV BHATACHA|website=www.webmallindia.com|accessdate=2 March 2019}}</ref> He was also part of famous Marathi play [[Mukkam Post Bombilwadi]].<ref>http://bollyduniya.com/marathi-natak/watch/5150/mukkam-post-bombilwadi-2003</ref>\n\nHe played one of the lead roles in Albattya Galbattya<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mumbaitheatreguide.com/dramas/marathi/albattya-galbattya-marathi-play-preview.asp#|title=ALBATTYA GALBATTYA Marathi Play/Drama|last=|first=|date=|website=www.mumbaitheatreguide.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archivedate=|accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref> and Iblis.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spotboye.com/marathi/marathi-news/iblis-scary-new-teaser-of-apurva-nemlekar-and-vaibhav-mangle-starrer-play-is-out-now/5e295a67d996471ad814ea27|title=Iblis: Scary New Teaser Of Apurva Nemlekar And Vaibhav Mangle Starrer Play Is Out Now|last=Naroji|first=Samruddhi|date=23 January 2020|website=www.spotboye.com|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archivedate=|accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|nm3642396}}\n*[https://www.tik-tok-videos.com/marathi-comedy/ Marathi Comedy Videos]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mangle, Vaibhav}}\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Marathi cinema]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Marathi theatre]]\n[[Category:Marathi actors]]\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n\n\n{{India-film-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use Indian E