c philosopher. Professor of Sanskrit, Jabalpur College. Conferred title of Rao Bahadur on 1st January 1910, in recognition of his learning and public services.<ref name=\"Who's Who in India, 1911 Coronation Edition, p 27\"> [https://ia801605.us.archive.org/6/items/in.ernet.dli.2015.209992/2015.209992.Whos-Who_text.pdf Who's Who 1911 Coronation Edition], Lucknow,  Newul Kishore Press, 1911 (page 27)</ref>     \n* Rao Bahadur Sir [[Kurma Venkata Reddy Naidu]], Chief Minister of Madras Presidency.\n*Rai Bahadur Satyen Nath (S.N.) Mukherjee, First Indian origin Deputy Commissioner of Indian Police, Calcutta. <ref>{{Cite book|last=Channa|first=Subhadra Mitra|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=Qak0AAAAQBAJ&pg=PA79&dq=Rai+Bahadur+S.N.+Mukherjee&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiTh_CcoLvoAhUb8HMBHTshAuUQ6AEIKzAB#v=onepage&q=Rai%20Bahadur%20S.N.%20Mukherjee&f=false|title=Gender in South Asia|last2=Channa|first2=Subhadra|date=2013-09-05|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-1-107-04361-9|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Gupta (IAS.)|first=G. S.|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=76ZIAAAAYAAJ&dq=Rai+Bahadur+S.N.+Mukherjee&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=S.N.+Mukherjee|title=Free Masonry in India|date=1991|publisher=G.S. Gupta|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Court|first=India Supreme|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=a4M2AAAAIAAJ&dq=Rai+Bahadur+S.N.+Mukherjee&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=Deputy+commissioner+S.N.+Mukherjee|title=Indian Factories & Labour Reports|date=1963|publisher=Law Publishing House.|language=en}}</ref>\n* Rao Bahadur [[A. Veeriya Vandayar]], philanthropist.\n* Rao Bahadur [[P. I. Chinnaswamy Pillai]], First Municipal Chairman - Palakkad.\n* Rao Bahadur [[C. Jambulingam Mudaliar]], Indian politician and freedom-fighter.\n* Rao Bahadur [[Ranchhodlal Chhotalal]], textile mill pioneer and philanthropist\n* Rao Bahadur Dharmapravartha [[Gubbi Thotadappa]] , Dharmachathra Founder, [[Karnataka]].\n* [[Chhotu Ram|Rao Bahadur Sir Chhotu Ram]], 